OL,3,CCoroner warns of dangers at home after
OL,4,Cchild's death
OL,6,FThe court heard that "unconsciousness
OL,7,Fcould have occurred in 10 seconds or
OL,8,Fless and death would have followed a
OL,9,Ffew minutes later".
OL,11,FThe coroner told the court: "This is
OL,12,Fone of the tragedies in this case...
OL,13,Faccidents can happen so quickly."
OL,15,FConcluding her findings, she
OL,16,Freiterated NHS safety advice,
OL,17,Fincluding ensuring that the cords of
OL,18,Fblinds and curtains are tied up and
OL,19,Fout of toddler's reach, to not leave
OL,20,Fany type of cord, or gym cord or
OL,21,Fdressing gown cords lying around.
OL,26,@nD@VOUqD@RO]sD@]OUuD@aO]
